Palindrome</FONT></SPAN></B></P>
<P style=3D"TEXT-ALIGN: center" class=3DMsoNormal align=3Dcenter><B=20
style=3D"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal">Input: </B><SPAN=20
style=3D"mso-bidi-font-weight: bold">standard =
input<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P style=3D"TEXT-ALIGN: center" class=3DMsoNormal align=3Dcenter><B=20
style=3D"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal">Output: </B>standard output</P>
<P style=3D"TEXT-ALIGN: center" class=3DMsoNormal align=3Dcenter><B=20
style=3D"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal">Time Limit: </B>8 seconds</P>
<P style=3D"TEXT-ALIGN: justify" class=3DMsoNormal><![if =
!supportEmptyParas]><![endif]>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></P>
<P style=3D"TEXT-ALIGN: justify" class=3DMsoNormal>By definition =
palindrome is a=20
string which is not changed when reversed. "MADAM" is a nice example of=20
palindrome. It is an easy job to test whether a given string is a =
palindrome or=20
not. But it may not be so easy to generate a palindrome. </P><BR=20
style=3D"mso-ignore: vglayout" clear=3Dall>
<P style=3D"TEXT-ALIGN: justify" class=3DMsoNormal>Here we will make a =
palindrome=20
generator which will take an input string and return a palindrome. You =
can=20
easily verify that for a string of length 'n', no more than (n-1) =
characters are=20
required to make it a palindrome. Consider "abcd" and its palindrome =
"abcdcba"=20
or "abc" and its palindrome "abcba". But life is not so easy for =
programmers!!=20
We always want optimal cost. And you have to find the minimum number of=20
characters required to make a given string to a palindrome if you are =
allowed to=20
insert characters at any position of the string. </P>
<P style=3D"TEXT-ALIGN: justify" class=3DMsoNormal><![if =
!supportEmptyParas]><![endif]>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></P>
<P style=3D"TEXT-ALIGN: justify" class=3DMsoNormal><B=20
style=3D"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><FONT =
size=3D5>Input</FONT></SPAN></B></P>
<P style=3D"TEXT-ALIGN: justify" class=3DMsoNormal>Each input line =
consists only of=20
lower case letters. The size of input string will be at most 1000. Input =
is=20
terminated by EOF. </P><BR>
<P style=3D"TEXT-ALIGN: justify" class=3DMsoNormal><B=20
style=3D"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><FONT =
size=3D5>Output</FONT></SPAN></B></P>
<P style=3D"TEXT-ALIGN: justify" class=3DMsoNormal>For each input print =
the minimum=20
number of characters and such a palindrome seperated by one space in a =
line.=20
There may be many such palindromes. Any one will be accepted.=20
<P style=3D"TEXT-ALIGN: justify" class=3DMsoNormal><B=20
style=3D"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN=20
style=3D"FONT-SIZE: 14pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"><![if =
!supportEmptyParas]><![endif]>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></B></P>
<P style=3D"TEXT-ALIGN: justify" class=3DMsoNormal><B=20
style=3D"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><FONT size=3D5>Sample=20
Input</FONT></SPAN></B></P><FONT size=3D3 =
face=3Dcourier></FONT><XMP>abcd
